# README – English

## About FoxPDF

FoxPDF is a native, cross-platform PDF compressor for macOS, iOS, and iPadOS. It reduces PDF file sizes by up to 95% — without any external services, cloud uploads, or internet connection.

FoxPDF is part of the **FoxSuite** app family and follows its unified design system (FoxTask · FoxTime · FoxVault · FoxPDF).

---

### 🔒 Privacy & Data Protection

> **All processing happens exclusively on your device.**
>
> No data is transmitted to external servers. No cloud upload, no analytics, no telemetry. Your documents never leave your device.
>
> Frameworks used: `CoreGraphics` · `PDFKit` · `ImageIO` *(all Apple-native, fully offline)*

---

## Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| PDF Compression | Up to 95% file size reduction via image downscaling and JPEG recompression |
| Quality Presets | Screen (72 dpi) · eBook (150 dpi) · Print (300 dpi) · High Quality (600 dpi) · Custom |
| Batch Processing | Compress any number of PDFs in a single run |
| Metadata Removal | Optionally strips author, creation date, keywords, producer |
| Custom Mode | Freely adjustable image quality (5–100%) and max resolution (72–600 dpi) |
| macOS: Drag & Drop | Drop files directly into the window |
| iOS/iPadOS: File Picker | System file picker with ShareSheet export |
| Results View | Before/after size and savings percentage per file |

## Typical Savings

| Preset | Quality | Max DPI | Savings (scan-heavy PDFs) |
|---|---|---|---|
| Screen | 25% | 72 | 85–95% |
| eBook | 50% | 150 | 60–80% |
| Print | 75% | 300 | 30–50% |
| High Quality | 92% | 600 | 10–25% |

## Requirements

- macOS 13 Ventura or later
- iOS / iPadOS 16.0 or later
- Xcode 15 or later
- Swift 5.9 / Swift 6 compatible

## Xcode Setup

### 1. Create Multiplatform Project

```
File → New → Project → Multiplatform → App
Product Name:  FoxPDF
Bundle ID:     com.yourname.foxpdf
Deployment:    macOS 13.0 · iOS 16.0
```

### 2. Add Files

| File | Contents |
|---|---|
| `FoxPDFApp.swift` | `@main` entry point |
| `PDFCompressor.swift` | Compression engine (platform-independent) |
| `FoxDesignSystem.swift` | FoxSuite colors & styles |
| `ContentView.swift` | Adaptive main UI (macOS + iOS) |
| `SharedViews.swift` | FoxFileRow, FoxResultCard, iOS SettingsSheet |

### 3. Entitlements (macOS Target)

```
App Sandbox: ON
File Access → User Selected Files: Read/Write
```

## Technical Architecture

Compression happens in three steps:

1. Each PDF page is rendered into a `CGBitmapContext` at the target DPI
2. The bitmap is reencoded as JPEG at the chosen quality via `CGImageDestination`
3. Recompressed pages are assembled into a new PDF via `CGContext`

```
FoxPDFApp.swift
  └── ContentView.swift          (platform-adaptive via #if os(macOS))
        ├── macOS: HSplitView    (DropZone | Settings | Results)
        └── iOS:   ScrollView    (Cards, Preset-Chips, FloatingButton)

PDFCompressor.swift              (@MainActor ObservableObject)
  └── FoxPDFEngine               (nonisolated – no AppKit/UIKit)
        ├── CoreGraphics PDF-Context
        ├── CGBitmapContext Downscaling
        └── CGImageDestination JPEG Recompression

FoxDesignSystem.swift            (Color extensions, Styles)
SharedViews.swift                (FoxFileRow, FoxResultCard, SettingsSheet)
```

> The original file is **never** modified. Output: `filename_compressed.pdf`

